The paper deals with the design of parameterized and exact algorithms, which suggests that it belongs to the category of theoretical computer science (cs). The use of representative sets for families of subsets and multisets suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the algorithm to the problem of minimal weight r-SIMPLE k-PATH suggests that it belongs to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The mention of a corollary related to lopsided universal sets suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of graph theory (cs.GT).
